quran[24]{c,v,t,f}:
  56,91,"Then there is safety and peace (from the Punishment of Allâh) for those on the right Hand."
  56,92,"But if he (the dying person) be of the denying (of the Resurrection), the erring (away from the Right Path of Islâmic Monotheism),"
  56,93,"Then for him is an entertainment with boiling water."
  68,25,"And they went in the morning with strong intention, thinking that they have power (to prevent the poor taking anything of the fruits therefrom)."
  68,26,"But when they saw the (garden), they said: "
  68,27,"(Then they said): "
  69,22,"In a lofty Paradise,"
  69,23,"The fruits in bunches whereof will be low and near at hand."
  69,24,"Eat and drink at ease for that which you have sent on before you in days past!"
  70,16,"Taking away (burning completely) the head skin!"
  70,17,"Calling{1} (all) such as turn their backs and turn away their faces (from Faith) [picking and swallowing them up from that great gathering of mankind on the Day of Resurrection just as a bird picks up a food-grain from the earth with its beak and swallows it up] (Tafsir Al-Qurtubî)",1:[{70:17} (i.e. the Hell will call out): "[O Kafir (O disbeliever in Allâh, His angels, His Books, His Messengers, Day of Resurrection and in Al-Qadar (Divine Preordainments), O Mushrik (O polytheist, disbeliever in the Oneness of Allâh).]
  70,18,"And collect (wealth) and hide it (from spending it in the Cause of Allâh)."
  71,13,"What is the matter with you, that [you fear not Allâh (His punishment), and] you hope not for reward (from Allâh or you believe not in His Oneness)."
  71,14,"While He has created you in (different) stages [i.e. first Nutfah, then ‘Alaqah and then Mudghah, see (V.23:13,14)]."
  71,15,"See you not how Allâh has created the seven heavens one above another?"
  72,10,"‘And we know not whether evil is intended for those on earth, or whether their Lord intends for them a Right Path."
  72,11,"‘There are among us some that are righteous, and some the contrary; we are groups having different ways (religious sects)."
  72,12,"‘And we think that we cannot escape (the punishment of) Allâh in the earth, nor can we escape Him by flight."
  73,4,"Or a little more. And recite the Qur’ân (aloud) in a slow, (pleasant tone and) style.{1}",1:[{73:4} See the footnote of {29:51}.]
  73,5,"Verily, We shall send down to you a weighty Word (i.e. obligations, laws)."
  73,6,"Verily, the rising by night (for Tahajjud prayer) is very hard and most potent and good for governing oneself, and most suitable for (understanding) the Word (of Allâh)."
  74,1,"O you (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) enveloped in garments!"
  74,2,"Arise and warn!"
  74,3,"And magnify your Lord (Allâh)!"